    "body": "I haven't used DMPlex before but I assume PETSc package recipe needs to be updated to support mesh generation.\r\n\r\nFrom [this page](https://www.caam.rice.edu/~mk51/fem.html):\r\n\r\n```\r\nYou might want to configure with\r\n\r\n--download-triangle --with-ctetgen\r\n--download-chaco --download-metis --download-parmetis\r\n--download-hdf5\r\nfor automatic mesh generation, partitioning, and output.\r\n```\r\n \r\nBefore looking into this, @balay could you provide some suggestions here? metis and parmetis already there. I don't see triangle, chaco, tetgen packages in Spack and wondering how easy they are to integrate.",
